# What are the different data types used in MySQL Database?

## Numerical Data Types

MySQL provides different numerical data types to store numeric values. These are mainly divided into exact and approximate numeric types. Exact numeric types such as INT, INTEGER, SMALLINT, DECIMAL, and NUMERIC store values with high precision and are commonly used when accuracy is important. Approximate numeric types such as FLOAT and DOUBLE are used for storing floating-point numbers where small rounding differences are acceptable. INT is commonly used for storing whole numbers like IDs, counts, and quantities, while DECIMAL is preferred for financial values that require accurate calculations.

## Date and Time Data Types

MySQL provides various date and time data types to store temporal information. These include DATE, TIME, DATETIME, TIMESTAMP, and YEAR. DATE stores only the date value, TIME stores time values, DATETIME stores both date and time together, and TIMESTAMP records date and time values with automatic updating features. These data types are useful for storing information such as birth dates, order dates, login times, and transaction timestamps.

## String Data Types

String data types are used to store character and text-based information. The main string types in MySQL are CHAR and VARCHAR. CHAR stores fixed-length strings, while VARCHAR stores variable-length strings and saves storage space. For example, VARCHAR can be used for storing names, addresses, emails, and other textual information.

## Binary and Variable String Data Types

BINARY and VARBINARY data types are used to store binary strings. BINARY stores fixed-length binary data, whereas VARBINARY stores variable-length binary values. These are mainly used when storing data such as encrypted information, files, or binary formats.

## BLOB and TEXT Data Types

BLOB and TEXT data types are used for storing large amounts of data. BLOB types include TINYBLOB, BLOB, MEDIUMBLOB, and LONGBLOB, which store binary data like images, videos, and files. TEXT types include TINYTEXT, TEXT, MEDIUMTEXT, and LONGTEXT, which store large text values such as descriptions, articles, and documents.

