# OLTP (Online Transaction Processing)

OLTP is a database system designed to handle daily business transactions. It manages operations such as inserting new records, updating existing data, and deleting records. Examples include banking systems, online shopping applications, and reservation systems. OLTP databases are usually normalized to reduce data duplication and maintain accuracy and consistency of data.

---

# OLAP (Online Analytical Processing)

OLAP is used for analyzing large amounts of historical data and generating reports for decision-making. It is commonly used in data warehouses and business intelligence systems. OLAP helps organizations identify trends, perform analysis, and make strategic decisions. It usually uses structures like star schema and snowflake schema to improve analytical query performance.
